Class PAES

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class PAES
extends MOStrategy
    PAES strategy.

    The Pareto Archived Evolution Strategy (PAES) is an evolution strategy (ES) to solve multi-objective problems.

    PAES is a (1+1) ES that uses a reference archive to compare the mutated individual with previously found non-dominated solutions in order to decide if the mutant replaces the current individual.

    Paper: J.D. Knowles, D.W. Corne, “Approximating the Nondominated Front Using the Pareto Archived Evolution Strategy”, Evolutionary Computation, vol. 8, no. 2, pp. 149-172. 2000.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:

    Author:

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

      • updateArchive

        public java.util.List<net.sf.jclec.IIndividual> updateArchive(java.util.List<net.sf.jclec.IIndividual> population,
                                                              java.util.List<net.sf.jclec.IIndividual> offspring,
                                                              java.util.List<net.sf.jclec.IIndividual> archive)
        Update the archive of solutions.

        In (1+1) PAES, the new individual can be add to the archive if it the archive is not full or if it belongs to a less crowding region. It requires the previous execution of the test() method, since that function determines both conditions.

        Specified by:
        updateArchive in class MOStrategy
        Parameters:
        population - Individuals within the current population.
        offspring - Individuals created by variation operators.
        archive - Individuals belonging to the current archive.
        Returns:
        List containing the new member of the archive.
